1
00:01:10,559 --> 00:01:11,639
Has the Chairman arrived yet?

2
00:01:12,239 --> 00:01:13,360
If we head over there right now,

3
00:01:13,480 --> 00:01:14,279
will we still make it in time?

4
00:01:14,919 --> 00:01:15,599
Don't worry.

5
00:01:15,599 --> 00:01:17,319
If we leave now, we'll have plenty of time.

6
00:01:17,800 --> 00:01:19,720
What is the Chairman's itinerary in China this time?

7
00:01:20,160 --> 00:01:21,879
The Chairman will go to Tongzhou Factory tomorrow

8
00:01:21,879 --> 00:01:22,959
for an on-site inspection.

9
00:01:23,360 --> 00:01:25,160
After Director Feng officially becomes a board member,

10
00:01:25,400 --> 00:01:26,760
he will join the board members in the evening.

11
00:01:26,760 --> 00:01:27,239
Wait a minute.

12
00:01:28,239 --> 00:01:30,239
Did you just say the inspection of Tongzhou Factory

13
00:01:30,480 --> 00:01:31,160
is tomorrow?

14
00:01:31,559 --> 00:01:32,120
Yes.

15
00:01:32,559 --> 00:01:33,400
So, Nelson,

16
00:01:33,400 --> 00:01:34,760
you'll be absent from the Board of Directors meeting tomorrow

17
00:01:34,919 --> 00:01:36,360
to personally accompany the president there?

18
00:01:36,720 --> 00:01:37,959
The workers are on strike.

19
00:01:38,599 --> 00:01:40,080
This will have a huge impact on the inspection.

20
00:01:40,639 --> 00:01:41,360
Don't worry.

21
00:01:41,720 --> 00:01:43,959
We've already taken care of this matter.

22
00:01:44,080 --> 00:01:44,839
How did you handle it?

23
00:01:44,839 --> 00:01:46,839
Director Feng took special measures.

24
00:01:48,680 --> 00:01:49,680
At this hour,

25
00:01:49,919 --> 00:01:51,360
it should have already started over there.

26
00:01:51,559 --> 00:01:52,959
Why didn't I know about this?

27
00:01:53,160 --> 00:01:54,279
Who gave Feng Ziang this authority?

28
00:01:55,120 --> 00:01:56,279
Secure our jobs!

29
00:01:56,720 --> 00:01:58,080
Secure our jobs!

30
00:01:58,360 --> 00:01:59,239
No to layoffs!

31
00:01:59,599 --> 00:02:00,199
Jiaqi.

32
00:02:00,199 --> 00:02:00,839
Uncle Du.

33
00:02:01,519 --> 00:02:02,800
Secure our jobs!

34
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:04,559
What brings you here today?

35
00:02:05,199 --> 00:02:06,559
President Gu asked me to get the accounting documents.

36
00:02:07,559 --> 00:02:08,639
I hope I'm not interrupting you.

37
00:02:09,639 --> 00:02:10,600
How could you be interrupting?

38
00:02:10,960 --> 00:02:11,759
As you can see,

39
00:02:12,080 --> 00:02:13,000
the boss isn't here.

40
00:02:13,279 --> 00:02:14,039
Our protest

41
00:02:14,360 --> 00:02:16,039
hasn't had any substantial effect.

42
00:02:16,240 --> 00:02:18,240
At least it shows the boss our stance.

43
00:02:19,279 --> 00:02:19,919
I hope so.

44
00:02:21,240 --> 00:02:22,240
Listen to me, everyone.

45
00:02:22,679 --> 00:02:23,679
Let's take a break first.

46
00:02:23,839 --> 00:02:24,679
Have some water.

47
00:02:25,839 --> 00:02:26,960
Come on, get up.

48
00:02:27,919 --> 00:02:28,720
Don't worry.

49
00:02:29,119 --> 00:02:30,279
Everything is proceeding as planned.

50
00:02:31,520 --> 00:02:32,360
At 1:00 PM,

51
00:02:32,720 --> 00:02:33,880
the group of workers I arranged

52
00:02:34,199 --> 00:02:36,320
will hold the protest representatives accountable,

53
00:02:38,160 --> 00:02:39,880
demanding they stop the protest immediately

54
00:02:39,880 --> 00:02:40,759
and resume production.

55
00:02:42,479 --> 00:02:44,240
This matter concerns the factory's future.

56
00:02:44,600 --> 00:02:45,600
How will it be resolved?

57
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:47,320
Let them argue it out among themselves first.

58
00:02:56,720 --> 00:02:58,039
Pick up the phone, Lin Jiaqi.

59
00:03:00,080 --> 00:03:01,559
Shouldn't you have your phone in your hand?

60
00:03:23,320 --> 00:03:24,039
Stop fighting!

61
00:03:26,800 --> 00:03:28,119
Lin Jiaqi!

62
00:03:38,440 --> 00:03:39,520
This is our big boss,

63
00:03:39,520 --> 00:03:40,479
Mr. Morse.

64
00:03:40,919 --> 00:03:43,160
Mr. Morse, this is Mr. Feng.

65
00:03:43,160 --> 00:03:44,520
And this is Mr. Hu.

66
00:03:47,399 --> 00:03:48,119
Hello.

67
00:03:48,720 --> 00:03:50,000
Nice to meet you.

68
00:03:50,360 --> 00:03:51,440
Your Chinese is really good.

69
00:03:51,720 --> 00:03:52,399
You flatter me.

70
00:03:52,919 --> 00:03:53,559
After you.

71
00:03:54,039 --> 00:03:54,679
After you.

72
00:04:01,039 --> 00:04:01,679
President Gu

73
00:04:04,679 --> 00:04:06,039
Jiaqi, are you okay?

74
00:04:06,800 --> 00:04:07,399
I'm fine.

75
00:04:07,639 --> 00:04:08,320
The doctor said

76
00:04:09,039 --> 00:04:10,160
it's just a mild concussion.

77
00:04:10,919 --> 00:04:12,199
It comes with dizziness and nausea,

78
00:04:12,559 --> 00:04:13,119
but

79
00:04:13,279 --> 00:04:14,080
it's nothing serious.

80
00:04:15,960 --> 00:04:16,760
That's good.

81
00:04:18,079 --> 00:04:18,839
But look at you.

82
00:04:19,399 --> 00:04:21,160
You look even worse than Jiaqi.

83
00:04:21,679 --> 00:04:23,040
It's like you were the one who got hit.

84
00:04:24,119 --> 00:04:25,679
Were you in such a hurry on your way here

85
00:04:25,839 --> 00:04:26,720
that you didn't even eat?

86
00:04:28,239 --> 00:04:30,119
Can you stop making me worry?

87
00:04:30,519 --> 00:04:31,440
You're all talk.

88
00:04:31,959 --> 00:04:32,920
I don't see you bringing any food.

89
00:04:33,079 --> 00:04:34,519
You were in such a rush when you called me,

90
00:04:34,519 --> 00:04:36,239
I... how could I think of bringing food?

91
00:04:36,839 --> 00:04:37,480
Oh, right.

92
00:04:37,760 --> 00:04:39,519
You need to call Director Liu right away.

93
00:04:40,160 --> 00:04:41,320
At such a critical moment,

94
00:04:41,320 --> 00:04:42,320
you stood the big boss up.

95
00:04:42,559 --> 00:04:44,000
I'm telling you, you're in big trouble this time.

96
00:04:44,359 --> 00:04:46,279
Director Liu has been nagging me all afternoon.

97
00:04:46,359 --> 00:04:47,720
Call her right now

98
00:04:47,920 --> 00:04:48,640
and apologize.

99
00:04:48,799 --> 00:04:49,399
It's a good chance

100
00:04:49,679 --> 00:04:50,799
to go out and get some fresh air.

101
00:04:51,640 --> 00:04:52,480
It hurts so much.

102
00:04:58,799 --> 00:05:00,320
It's him. Look, everyone, it's him.

103
00:05:00,519 --> 00:05:00,760
Yeah.

104
00:05:00,760 --> 00:05:01,440
This is the guy. It's him.

105
00:05:01,519 --> 00:05:02,200
That's him.

106
00:05:03,239 --> 00:05:04,200
That guy named Gu something.

107
00:05:04,679 --> 00:05:05,600
He's the one from...

108
00:05:06,279 --> 00:05:07,720
The guy sent by Rosenmoss Company.

109
00:05:08,640 --> 00:05:09,480
What are you doing here?

110
00:05:09,920 --> 00:05:10,920
You have the nerve to show up?

111
00:05:12,040 --> 00:05:12,959
Here to laugh at us?

112
00:05:13,320 --> 00:05:14,239
Are you even human?

113
00:05:14,600 --> 00:05:15,559
We workers went on strike

114
00:05:15,720 --> 00:05:17,160
just to defend our rights.

115
00:05:17,359 --> 00:05:18,480
If you hadn't ignored us,

116
00:05:18,640 --> 00:05:20,040
it wouldn't have led to today's clash.

117
00:05:20,040 --> 00:05:21,079
Look. Do you see this?

118
00:05:21,480 --> 00:05:22,440
So many people got hurt.

119
00:05:24,079 --> 00:05:25,119
You feel a great sense of achievement, right?

120
00:05:25,399 --> 00:05:26,320
A great sense of achievement.

121
00:05:27,000 --> 00:05:27,640
Fellow workers!

122
00:05:27,720 --> 00:05:28,239
Fellow workers!

123
00:05:28,239 --> 00:05:29,079
Calm down. Don't get worked up.

124
00:05:29,359 --> 00:05:30,359
Let's talk this out. Let's talk.

125
00:05:30,799 --> 00:05:31,440
Talk about what?

126
00:05:31,799 --> 00:05:32,600
Who told you to do this?

127
00:05:33,559 --> 00:05:34,239
What did you say?

128
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:36,480
Who told you to risk your lives

129
00:05:36,720 --> 00:05:37,679
on something so hopeless?

130
00:05:38,440 --> 00:05:38,880
You...

131
00:05:41,480 --> 00:05:42,519
It's just a factory, isn't it?

132
00:05:43,720 --> 00:05:44,720
You just got fired, didn't you?

133
00:05:45,559 --> 00:05:46,600
Even if you're out of money,

134
00:05:47,239 --> 00:05:48,000
is it worth it?

135
00:05:48,440 --> 00:05:49,600
Is it worth it to fight to the death

136
00:05:49,920 --> 00:05:51,160
over this matter?

137
00:05:52,040 --> 00:05:52,720
Why?

138
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:54,760
Why?

139
00:05:57,399 --> 00:05:58,519
I'll tell you why.

140
00:05:59,399 --> 00:06:01,040
Because we want to live with dignity.

141
00:06:02,920 --> 00:06:04,239
You heartless bastards

142
00:06:04,559 --> 00:06:06,000
never treated us like human beings.

143
00:06:07,040 --> 00:06:08,399
It's exactly because we want to live with dignity

144
00:06:08,519 --> 00:06:09,519
that we fought back.

145
00:06:10,320 --> 00:06:11,600
Are you satisfied with that answer?

146
00:06:15,559 --> 00:06:16,600
But do you think

147
00:06:18,239 --> 00:06:19,880
this will make them treat you like humans?

148
00:06:21,959 --> 00:06:23,160
After what happened today,

149
00:06:23,160 --> 00:06:24,160
don't you all understand?

150
00:06:26,239 --> 00:06:27,839
You can't change anything at all.

151
00:06:28,040 --> 00:06:29,239
What did you say? Say that again!

152
00:06:29,799 --> 00:06:30,559
Say it again!

153
00:06:32,079 --> 00:06:33,160
I'm asking you to give up.

154
00:06:37,839 --> 00:06:38,839
Fighting against us,

155
00:06:40,480 --> 00:06:41,920
guys who aren't even human,

156
00:06:44,359 --> 00:06:45,839
you'll only lose time and time again.

157
00:06:46,320 --> 00:06:47,200
This is too much!

158
00:06:48,799 --> 00:06:49,600
You jerk!

159
00:06:49,760 --> 00:06:50,760
I'll beat you to death today!

160
00:06:50,839 --> 00:06:51,399
Beat you to death!

161
00:06:51,760 --> 00:06:52,079
Jerk!

162
00:06:52,079 --> 00:06:52,519
Stop!

163
00:06:52,640 --> 00:06:53,200
Beat you to death!

164
00:06:53,359 --> 00:06:53,920
Don't hit him!

165
00:06:55,320 --> 00:06:55,760
Jiaqi.

166
00:06:55,760 --> 00:06:58,000
Uncle Liu, Xiao Li, everyone, please calm down.

167
00:06:58,640 --> 00:06:59,799
Jiaqi, stay out of this.

168
00:07:00,519 --> 00:07:01,279
Uncle Du.

169
00:07:01,640 --> 00:07:03,279
Jiaqi, he's being disrespectful

170
00:07:03,480 --> 00:07:04,359
and looking down on us.

171
00:07:04,359 --> 00:07:05,399
And you're still defending him?

172
00:07:05,720 --> 00:07:06,720
Uncle Du, listen to me.

173
00:07:07,239 --> 00:07:08,239
What he just said

174
00:07:08,239 --> 00:07:10,200
was purely because he felt it wasn't worth you getting hurt.

175
00:07:10,839 --> 00:07:12,600
Although his way of expressing it was a bit extreme,

176
00:07:12,839 --> 00:07:13,959
he absolutely meant no harm.

177
00:07:16,519 --> 00:07:17,839
I apologize to everyone on his behalf.

178
00:07:18,839 --> 00:07:19,839
I'm sorry.

179
00:07:21,160 --> 00:07:22,119
I'm sorry.

180
00:07:29,679 --> 00:07:30,880
The incident at Tongzhou Factory yesterday,

181
00:07:30,880 --> 00:07:31,799
how was it handled?

182
00:07:32,519 --> 00:07:33,279
Is everything settled?

183
00:07:33,920 --> 00:07:34,640
Don't worry.

184
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:36,559
It's been taken care of perfectly.

185
00:07:37,000 --> 00:07:37,959
They handled the matter

186
00:07:37,959 --> 00:07:38,679
and resolved it

187
00:07:38,679 --> 00:07:40,079
cleanly and neatly.

188
00:07:40,600 --> 00:07:42,440
The interview this afternoon will definitely be fine.

189
00:07:44,279 --> 00:07:44,959
Were there any injuries?

190
00:07:45,720 --> 00:07:46,320
With this kind of thing,

191
00:07:46,519 --> 00:07:47,920
the main goal was just to scare them a bit.

192
00:07:48,239 --> 00:07:50,160
A few injuries are inevitable.

193
00:07:50,279 --> 00:07:51,760
Besides, the relevant authorities have stepped in,

194
00:07:51,880 --> 00:07:52,920
and the families have been pacified.

195
00:07:53,920 --> 00:07:54,600
However,

196
00:07:54,880 --> 00:07:55,640
I heard that

197
00:07:56,040 --> 00:07:57,519
when our people went there yesterday,

198
00:07:58,239 --> 00:07:59,720
someone from our company was also there

199
00:08:00,440 --> 00:08:01,440
and got slightly injured.

200
00:08:02,399 --> 00:08:03,480
Someone from our company?

201
00:08:04,119 --> 00:08:04,799
Who?

202
00:08:05,640 --> 00:08:07,559
It... It was Secretary Lin.

203
00:08:10,239 --> 00:08:11,480
Are you talking about Lin Jiaqi?

204
00:08:11,720 --> 00:08:12,320
Yes.

205
00:08:27,200 --> 00:08:27,880
Jiaqi,

206
00:08:28,640 --> 00:08:29,600
why didn't you answer my calls?

207
00:08:32,080 --> 00:08:33,000
I didn't notice them just now.

208
00:08:33,640 --> 00:08:34,559
How are your injuries?

209
00:08:34,880 --> 00:08:35,679
Are they serious?

210
00:08:36,280 --> 00:08:37,080
What did the hospital say?

211
00:08:38,599 --> 00:08:40,119
You shouldn't have come to work if you're injured.

212
00:08:40,760 --> 00:08:41,599
Rest at home for a few days.

213
00:08:43,520 --> 00:08:44,719
How did you know I was injured?

214
00:08:51,919 --> 00:08:53,320
I have something to ask you.

215
00:08:55,320 --> 00:08:56,599
Please answer me honestly.

216
00:09:01,840 --> 00:09:03,320
There are a lot of rumors out there.

217
00:09:03,679 --> 00:09:04,960
I believe you've already heard them.

218
00:09:05,919 --> 00:09:06,719
They say

219
00:09:07,119 --> 00:09:08,960
you sent people to Tongzhou Factory to beat people up.

220
00:09:09,679 --> 00:09:10,400
Is that true?

221
00:09:11,559 --> 00:09:12,359
Is it real?

222
00:09:12,799 --> 00:09:13,840
Or is it just a rumor?

223
00:09:14,479 --> 00:09:15,320
Tell me.

224
00:09:17,679 --> 00:09:18,400
That's right.

225
00:09:19,080 --> 00:09:20,400
I ordered it.

226
00:09:21,599 --> 00:09:22,760
I knew I couldn't hide it for long.

227
00:09:23,159 --> 00:09:24,000
You'd find out sooner or later.

228
00:09:28,559 --> 00:09:29,599
You really did it.

229
00:09:31,239 --> 00:09:32,320
Why would you do such a thing?

230
00:09:32,960 --> 00:09:33,559
What kind of problem

231
00:09:33,559 --> 00:09:35,000
can't be solved in a civilized way?

232
00:09:35,359 --> 00:09:36,359
Why must you use violence?

233
00:09:37,039 --> 00:09:38,599
Many of them are already injured

234
00:09:39,880 --> 00:09:40,919
and have lost hope.

235
00:09:41,559 --> 00:09:42,559
What were you thinking?

236
00:09:42,960 --> 00:09:44,640
Do you want me to take you to the hospital to see them?

237
00:09:44,960 --> 00:09:46,359
I know. I know it all.

238
00:09:46,840 --> 00:09:47,799
But it was bound to happen sooner or later.

239
00:09:48,039 --> 00:09:49,280
Sooner or later?

240
00:09:49,919 --> 00:09:51,479
Even if I didn't order it,

241
00:09:51,880 --> 00:09:53,119
someone else would have done it.

242
00:09:53,880 --> 00:09:55,239
Tongzhou Factory can't be saved.

243
00:09:56,239 --> 00:09:57,280
These people are just acting in vain.

244
00:09:58,080 --> 00:09:58,919
Zi'ang,

245
00:10:00,479 --> 00:10:02,200
you're becoming more and more unrecognizable to me.

246
00:10:03,280 --> 00:10:04,599
I feel like you're a stranger.

247
00:10:05,239 --> 00:10:06,520
You even make me feel scared.

248
00:10:09,479 --> 00:10:10,280
Before this,

249
00:10:10,799 --> 00:10:12,520
I always thought I knew you well.

250
00:10:13,520 --> 00:10:14,280
It seems I was wrong.

251
00:10:15,599 --> 00:10:16,440
Don't be like this, Jiaqi.

252
00:10:17,280 --> 00:10:18,280
If even you act like this,

253
00:10:18,919 --> 00:10:19,799
I'll be very sad.

254
00:10:21,039 --> 00:10:22,719
I have my reasons for doing all this.

255
00:10:23,479 --> 00:10:25,039
So many people out there hate me and despise me,

256
00:10:25,760 --> 00:10:26,799
but I at least thought

257
00:10:27,239 --> 00:10:28,200
you could understand me.

258
00:10:30,280 --> 00:10:31,679
I will never be able to understand.

259
00:10:32,799 --> 00:10:33,679
Director Feng,

260
00:10:36,200 --> 00:10:37,320
for today's Board of Directors meeting

261
00:10:37,679 --> 00:10:39,000
and the subsequent inauguration ceremony,

262
00:10:39,880 --> 00:10:41,000
I will prepare well

263
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:42,119
and arrange everything perfectly.

264
00:10:42,400 --> 00:10:43,520
Because this is my job.

265
00:10:43,679 --> 00:10:44,840
But I won't congratulate you.

266
00:10:45,640 --> 00:10:47,479
I can't be happy for you from the bottom of my heart.

267
00:10:48,039 --> 00:10:48,640
So,

268
00:10:49,400 --> 00:10:50,719
don't ask me to do that anymore.

269
00:10:51,799 --> 00:10:52,559
Director Feng.

270
00:11:31,719 --> 00:11:32,200
Hello.

271
00:11:34,159 --> 00:11:35,200
So many people here to welcome me.

272
00:11:35,799 --> 00:11:36,640
You're too kind.

273
00:11:37,760 --> 00:11:38,440
Wait.

274
00:11:38,919 --> 00:11:41,039
I thought you weren't coming today.

275
00:11:41,640 --> 00:11:42,440
Is there a problem?

276
00:11:43,280 --> 00:11:44,520
Isn't the Board of Directors meeting today?

277
00:11:45,359 --> 00:11:47,359
I'm here to cast my precious vote.

278
00:11:47,599 --> 00:11:48,440
Fair enough.

279
00:11:48,599 --> 00:11:49,520
It's just that I heard

280
00:11:49,520 --> 00:11:50,919
you weren't attending the Board of Directors meeting today.

281
00:11:51,239 --> 00:11:53,039
It seems you and the president of Rosenmoss Company

282
00:11:53,039 --> 00:11:54,000
went on a site visit.

283
00:11:54,760 --> 00:11:55,719
I suddenly didn't want to go.

284
00:11:56,359 --> 00:11:57,119
So I stood him up.

285
00:11:57,520 --> 00:11:58,760
What are you trying to do now?

286
00:12:01,039 --> 00:12:02,039
What am I trying to do?

287
00:12:03,479 --> 00:12:04,440
You'll find out in a moment.

288
00:12:16,080 --> 00:12:16,880
Where should I sit?

289
00:12:20,200 --> 00:12:20,960
Over here.

290
00:12:23,840 --> 00:12:25,239
Jiaqi, are you in charge of

291
00:12:25,479 --> 00:12:26,280
taking the minutes today?

292
00:12:26,599 --> 00:12:27,239
Do your best.

293
00:12:55,880 --> 00:12:56,400
All right.

294
00:12:57,080 --> 00:12:57,719
Everyone,

295
00:12:58,280 --> 00:12:59,280
the incumbent directors

296
00:12:59,559 --> 00:13:00,559
have all arrived.

297
00:13:01,320 --> 00:13:02,159
So today, we will

298
00:13:02,599 --> 00:13:04,880
begin our Board of Directors meeting.

299
00:13:05,840 --> 00:13:06,840
Today's agenda is

300
00:13:07,280 --> 00:13:08,760
to elect a new Chief Executive Officer.

301
00:13:09,039 --> 00:13:09,760
Currently,

302
00:13:10,159 --> 00:13:11,200
the candidate for Chief Executive Officer

303
00:13:11,200 --> 00:13:11,919
is only one person,

304
00:13:12,400 --> 00:13:14,280
which is our Mr. Feng Zi'ang.

305
00:13:15,559 --> 00:13:16,359
Now then,

306
00:13:16,640 --> 00:13:18,679
are there any other self-nominations

307
00:13:19,359 --> 00:13:20,039
or

308
00:13:20,359 --> 00:13:21,719
recommended candidates?

309
00:13:26,799 --> 00:13:28,840
If there are no new recommendations,

310
00:13:29,200 --> 00:13:31,159
then we will prepare to vote.

311
00:13:31,400 --> 00:13:32,239
Wait a minute.

312
00:13:37,000 --> 00:13:37,840
I propose

313
00:13:38,520 --> 00:13:39,520
adding one more candidate.

314
00:13:40,880 --> 00:13:41,400
Who?

315
00:13:42,960 --> 00:13:43,840
Me.

316
00:13:45,039 --> 00:13:45,840
Director Gu,

317
00:13:46,200 --> 00:13:47,640
you want to be a candidate too?

318
00:13:48,479 --> 00:13:49,080
What's wrong?

319
00:13:49,400 --> 00:13:50,200
Is there a problem?

320
00:13:51,320 --> 00:13:51,960
Gu Tiancheng,

321
00:13:52,640 --> 00:13:53,239
are you scared?

322
00:13:54,159 --> 00:13:55,960
Scared of losing to me at the Shareholders' meeting?

323
00:13:56,119 --> 00:13:56,880
How could I be?

324
00:13:58,559 --> 00:13:59,520
I was just wondering,

325
00:13:59,960 --> 00:14:01,200
what is your intention in doing this?

326
00:14:02,479 --> 00:14:04,000
I only have one intention in doing this.

327
00:14:05,000 --> 00:14:06,400
I want to save this company.

328
00:14:07,719 --> 00:14:08,599
What did you say?

329
00:14:09,880 --> 00:14:11,039
Darn it, is your brain broken?

330
00:14:11,440 --> 00:14:12,000
That's right.

331
00:14:12,599 --> 00:14:13,640
My brain is broken, darn it.

332
00:14:14,559 --> 00:14:15,919
Yesterday at the Tongzhou Factory,

333
00:14:16,359 --> 00:14:17,799
I saw something I shouldn't have seen.

334
00:14:18,520 --> 00:14:19,760
I'm still full of anger even now.

335
00:14:20,880 --> 00:14:22,200
Now is not the time to bring this up.

336
00:14:26,200 --> 00:14:27,359
Since you want to challenge me so much,

337
00:14:28,320 --> 00:14:29,200
then let's give it a try.

338
00:14:29,719 --> 00:14:31,200
But you, an external director,

339
00:14:31,760 --> 00:14:33,239
coming to our company like a migratory bird,

340
00:14:34,239 --> 00:14:35,479
are just an empty shell.

341
00:14:36,799 --> 00:14:37,440
I'm afraid

342
00:14:37,799 --> 00:14:39,200
you still don't understand the company's business.

343
00:14:40,039 --> 00:14:40,640
Think about it,

344
00:14:41,640 --> 00:14:43,000
who would elect you as Chief Executive Officer?

345
00:14:46,239 --> 00:14:47,000
Who said

346
00:14:47,359 --> 00:14:48,880
that at today's Shareholders' meeting

347
00:14:48,880 --> 00:14:49,719
we are going to vote?

348
00:14:50,640 --> 00:14:51,400
What do you mean?

349
00:14:52,640 --> 00:14:53,559
What exactly do you want?

350
00:15:00,679 --> 00:15:01,799
Open it and see for yourself.

351
00:15:02,400 --> 00:15:04,159
Inside is my shareholder proposal.

352
00:15:04,640 --> 00:15:05,599
The subject of the proposal

353
00:15:06,119 --> 00:15:07,400
is the election of the Chief Executive Officer.

354
00:15:11,520 --> 00:15:12,320
What?

355
00:15:13,599 --> 00:15:14,159
Could it be that you...

356
00:15:14,359 --> 00:15:14,960
That's right.

357
00:15:15,320 --> 00:15:16,960
The shares my uncle previously pledged

358
00:15:16,960 --> 00:15:17,719
to the brokerage,

359
00:15:18,719 --> 00:15:19,960
I bought them all on a whim.

360
00:15:21,039 --> 00:15:21,960
In other words,

361
00:15:22,760 --> 00:15:23,479
I,

362
00:15:24,039 --> 00:15:25,000
Gu Tiancheng,

363
00:15:26,200 --> 00:15:28,239
am now the largest shareholder of Feimanchi.

364
00:15:29,799 --> 00:15:30,320
Director Gu,

365
00:15:30,760 --> 00:15:31,919
why are you so impulsive?

366
00:15:32,280 --> 00:15:33,039
Why did you suddenly

367
00:15:33,039 --> 00:15:34,159
buy so many shares?

368
00:15:34,400 --> 00:15:35,479
If the company goes bankrupt,

369
00:15:35,479 --> 00:15:36,159
your shares will...

370
00:15:37,400 --> 00:15:39,119
But the company hasn't gone bankrupt yet.

371
00:15:40,719 --> 00:15:41,320
Therefore,

372
00:15:41,679 --> 00:15:42,520
those debt collectors

373
00:15:42,719 --> 00:15:44,159
before the company goes bankrupt,

374
00:15:44,840 --> 00:15:46,359
have no power at all.

375
00:15:47,640 --> 00:15:48,159
You,

376
00:15:49,320 --> 00:15:50,119
and me,

377
00:15:51,119 --> 00:15:52,599
we will bet on the Chief Executive Officer position

378
00:15:53,159 --> 00:15:54,440
and have a head-on confrontation.

379
00:15:55,559 --> 00:15:57,400
Right at the Shareholders' meeting.

380
00:16:00,000 --> 00:16:01,359
Why exactly are you doing this?

381
00:16:08,880 --> 00:16:09,919
Because I don't know

382
00:16:11,719 --> 00:16:13,559
why I should keep living like before.

383
00:16:14,880 --> 00:16:16,280
There is no middle ground in life,

384
00:16:17,479 --> 00:16:18,799
nor is it possible to have everything.

385
00:16:21,039 --> 00:16:22,640
So you must choose a path,

386
00:16:24,760 --> 00:16:25,880
and walk it to the very end.

387
00:16:30,799 --> 00:16:32,159
So from now on,

388
00:16:34,880 --> 00:16:36,599
I am going to save this factory.

389
00:16:45,960 --> 00:16:46,520
Come in.

390
00:16:53,000 --> 00:16:53,599
President Gu.

391
00:16:53,640 --> 00:16:54,520
Don't say anything.

392
00:16:57,200 --> 00:16:57,840
Thank you so much.

393
00:17:01,200 --> 00:17:02,719
I've noticed that whenever I run into you,

394
00:17:03,440 --> 00:17:04,640
nothing goes right.

395
00:17:07,839 --> 00:17:10,239
My life is a complete mess right now.

396
00:17:11,599 --> 00:17:13,040
After making this decision today,

397
00:17:13,880 --> 00:17:15,599
there will still be many, many problems

398
00:17:15,599 --> 00:17:16,560
that I'll have to face.

399
00:17:17,239 --> 00:17:18,239
Didn't I tell you?

400
00:17:19,160 --> 00:17:20,599
No matter what happens,

401
00:17:21,680 --> 00:17:22,839
I will stay by your side,

402
00:17:24,119 --> 00:17:25,040
protect you,

403
00:17:25,599 --> 00:17:26,319
and help you,

404
00:17:27,079 --> 00:17:27,839
so you can become

405
00:17:28,680 --> 00:17:29,719
just like your father.

406
00:17:33,560 --> 00:17:34,199
What's wrong?

407
00:17:37,400 --> 00:17:39,439
My heart suddenly feels a bit uncomfortable.

408
00:17:41,319 --> 00:17:43,239
Can I just lean on you like this?

409
00:17:48,400 --> 00:17:49,920
Since I'm already leaning on you,

410
00:17:50,719 --> 00:17:52,040
could you maybe

411
00:17:52,760 --> 00:17:54,119
pat my back while you're at it?

412
00:18:29,760 --> 00:18:30,520
Director.

413
00:18:31,439 --> 00:18:32,119
Director.

414
00:18:33,199 --> 00:18:34,280
Contact Director Liu immediately.

415
00:18:35,000 --> 00:18:36,119
Tell her about the current situation

416
00:18:36,719 --> 00:18:37,640
and arrange a time to meet.

417
00:18:38,000 --> 00:18:38,439
No,

418
00:18:38,599 --> 00:18:39,520
please calm down first.

419
00:18:39,680 --> 00:18:40,599
Please don't panic.

420
00:18:40,920 --> 00:18:42,160
If not now, when should I panic?

421
00:18:42,640 --> 00:18:43,920
Can't you see the current situation clearly?

422
00:18:44,319 --> 00:18:45,680
The person eyeing this position

423
00:18:46,079 --> 00:18:47,199
is Gu Tiancheng, who is sharpening his knife

424
00:18:47,199 --> 00:18:48,520
against the heroes who restored order!

425
00:18:49,319 --> 00:18:50,239
Can't you see that?

426
00:18:50,560 --> 00:18:52,280
Will he just let the current directors off the hook?

427
00:18:52,400 --> 00:18:53,599
He came here for revenge.

428
00:18:55,160 --> 00:18:56,040
He is the one.

429
00:18:56,479 --> 00:18:57,959
He wants to be the Chief Executive Officer!

430
00:18:58,280 --> 00:18:59,880
You're right, you're right.

431
00:19:07,079 --> 00:19:08,760
If you still want to keep your current position,

432
00:19:09,800 --> 00:19:10,719
take action immediately.

433
00:19:10,959 --> 00:19:11,359
Okay.

434
00:19:11,560 --> 00:19:12,439
Right away.

435
00:19:13,479 --> 00:19:14,640
I'll call Director Liu right now.

436
00:19:14,920 --> 00:19:15,560
Make the call.

437
00:19:34,520 --> 00:19:35,680
Hello, Uncle Du.

438
00:19:36,599 --> 00:19:37,239
Jiaqi.

439
00:19:37,839 --> 00:19:38,680
How are you feeling?

440
00:19:39,319 --> 00:19:40,199
Are your injuries better?

441
00:19:40,880 --> 00:19:41,479
Much better.

442
00:19:41,719 --> 00:19:43,040
I'm sorry for making you worry.

443
00:19:43,520 --> 00:19:44,040
Well,

444
00:19:45,000 --> 00:19:46,800
could you come down to the factory?

445
00:19:47,199 --> 00:19:48,199
During the strike the other day,

446
00:19:48,560 --> 00:19:50,359
didn't you lose your bag?

447
00:19:51,280 --> 00:19:51,959
You found it?

448
00:19:52,520 --> 00:19:54,040
I sure did.

449
00:19:54,800 --> 00:19:55,239
Okay.

450
00:19:55,359 --> 00:19:56,040
See you later.

451
00:19:57,199 --> 00:19:57,760
Bye.

452
00:20:01,880 --> 00:20:02,359
Lucy.

453
00:20:03,000 --> 00:20:03,599
President Gu.

454
00:20:06,640 --> 00:20:07,599
Here is the gift you asked for.

455
00:20:08,000 --> 00:20:08,560
Thank you.

456
00:20:08,719 --> 00:20:09,359
You're welcome.

457
00:20:11,079 --> 00:20:11,719
Oh my god.

458
00:20:12,199 --> 00:20:12,920
What is this?

459
00:20:14,280 --> 00:20:15,479
You spent so much time preparing a gift,

460
00:20:15,599 --> 00:20:16,640
and it's just a bunch of lollipops?

461
00:20:17,119 --> 00:20:18,079
What's wrong with lollipops?

462
00:20:18,359 --> 00:20:19,560
They look good and taste good.

463
00:20:19,920 --> 00:20:20,640
Besides,

464
00:20:20,760 --> 00:20:22,160
they're my favorite thing.

465
00:20:22,439 --> 00:20:24,079
Come on, can't you use your head a little?

466
00:20:24,479 --> 00:20:26,119
Have you never given a girl a gift before?

467
00:20:26,119 --> 00:20:26,719
What?

468
00:20:27,040 --> 00:20:27,760
You think you're an expert?

469
00:20:28,439 --> 00:20:28,959
No,

470
00:20:29,079 --> 00:20:29,760
at the very least, you should

471
00:20:29,760 --> 00:20:31,040
give Jiaqi something she likes.

472
00:20:31,040 --> 00:20:32,520
Giving her lollipops that you like,

473
00:20:32,520 --> 00:20:33,239
what kind of sense does that make?

474
00:20:33,479 --> 00:20:35,040
You're asking for a beating like this, you know?

475
00:20:36,280 --> 00:20:37,040
Is that really how it works?

476
00:20:37,199 --> 00:20:38,199
Of course it is.

477
00:20:38,520 --> 00:20:40,199
You need to understand these basic principles.

478
00:20:40,599 --> 00:20:41,239
Also,

479
00:20:41,400 --> 00:20:43,000
your progress right now is way too slow.

480
00:20:43,359 --> 00:20:44,640
What era do you think we're in?

481
00:20:44,839 --> 00:20:46,680
It's all about speed, speed, speed.

482
00:20:46,959 --> 00:20:48,319
You can't be this slow.

483
00:20:49,479 --> 00:20:50,760
All of this

484
00:20:51,520 --> 00:20:52,479
is all because

485
00:20:53,359 --> 00:20:54,640
you've never been in a relationship.

486
00:21:01,479 --> 00:21:03,359
Today is the last day of Jiaqi's time off.

487
00:21:03,719 --> 00:21:04,599
I'm warning you,

488
00:21:04,680 --> 00:21:05,560
don't bother me.

489
00:21:05,800 --> 00:21:06,520
If you have anything to say,

490
00:21:06,520 --> 00:21:07,359
we'll talk tomorrow.

491
00:21:07,680 --> 00:21:08,439
Okay, okay, okay.

492
00:21:08,439 --> 00:21:09,359
Go, go, go.

493
00:21:09,719 --> 00:21:10,599
Throw those lollipops away.

494
00:21:11,119 --> 00:21:11,760
How embarrassing.

495
00:21:17,560 --> 00:21:18,079
Hello?

496
00:21:19,160 --> 00:21:19,800
It's me.

497
00:21:20,959 --> 00:21:21,640
What?
